Two robbery and hijacking suspects were arrested after a failed attempt of robbing Cresta mall. The SAPS spokesman, captain Kay Makhubele told Daily Sun that four suspects were driving a white Toyota Etios and hijacked an Opel Corsa in Cresta Mall's parking area. "On their way out they robbed a couple of their cell phones and other items," said Makhubela. But they did not get away with it. Just before they exited the Mall, the suspects were met by the police and security guards then a shoot out took place, where one suspect caught a bullet and taken to hospital. "He's under police guard and another suspect was arrested. The other two suspects fled on foot," said Makhubele. One firearm was recovered and some items robbed was also recovered with the hijacked corsa. Police established that the getaway car used was an Uber taxi.  